WEBVTT

00:02.623 --> 00:05.046
Meredith: I AM FINE.
I AM HAPPY TO BE HERE.

00:05.046 --> 00:07.468
TRULY,
I HAVE BEEN THROUGH A LOT,

00:07.468 --> 00:09.800
AND I'M LUCKY TO BE ALIVE,

00:09.800 --> 00:12.053
AND I'M LUCKY TO BE OKAY,
AND I GET THAT.

00:12.053 --> 00:15.346
SO, YES,
I'M JUST HAPPY TO BE HERE.

00:15.346 --> 00:17.518
GREAT.

00:17.518 --> 00:19.520
YOU KNOW, DOCTOR,
MOST SURGEONS,

00:19.520 --> 00:23.644
UH, GET KIND OF RANKLED
AT HOSPITAL-MANDATED THERAPY.

00:23.644 --> 00:25.146
BAILEY'S JUST
LOOKING OUT FOR ME.

00:25.146 --> 00:26.647
I KNOW THE DRILL.

00:26.647 --> 00:28.859
SO THIS SHOULD BE QUICK.

00:28.859 --> 00:31.031
YOU KNOW,
YOU CHOSE THE SHORT STRAW,

00:31.031 --> 00:32.823
OR THE --
IS IT THE LONG STRAW?

00:32.823 --> 00:34.285
WHATEVER THE GOOD STRAW IS.

00:34.285 --> 00:36.417
[ LAUGHS ]

00:36.417 --> 00:38.329
[ HORN BLARING ]

00:38.329 --> 00:40.791
LAY OFF THE DAMN HORN,
WILL YA?

00:40.791 --> 00:42.753
[ SIGHS ]
GOD, CARPOOL SUCKS.

00:42.753 --> 00:44.044
HANG ON.
IS WILSON COMING?

00:44.044 --> 00:45.716
I THINK SO.
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
YOU THINK SO?

00:45.716 --> 00:48.299
I CAN'T -- LOOK,
SHE'S ALL OVER THE PLACE.

00:48.299 --> 00:50.091
I DON'T EVEN KNOW WHY
SHE LET ME BACK IN THE HOUSE.

00:50.091 --> 00:51.552
WE BARELY TALK,
WHICH IS PROBABLY GOOD

00:51.552 --> 00:53.304
BECAUSE IT'S FEWER CHANCES
I'LL PISS HER OFF AGAIN.

00:53.304 --> 00:55.266
THAT'S PATHETIC.
WHAT'S HER PROBLEM?

00:55.266 --> 00:57.178
SHE'S IN A MOOD.
STILL?

00:57.178 --> 00:58.309
[ HORN BLARES ]

00:58.309 --> 00:59.850
I SAID TO TELL HER
THAT I NEEDED A MINUTE.

00:59.850 --> 01:03.023
YOU DIDN'T TELL ME THAT.
YES, I DID.
YOU DIDN'T LISTEN.

01:03.023 --> 01:05.446
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]
SO DONE WITH CARPOOL.

01:05.446 --> 01:07.238
[ TIRES SQUEAL ]

01:10.861 --> 01:13.114
[ SIREN WAILING ]

01:13.114 --> 01:15.406
INCOMING.
20 MINUTES, CHEST PAINS.

01:15.406 --> 01:17.698
I'LL TAKE IT. PAGE CARDIO --
ANYONE BUT RIGGS.

01:17.698 --> 01:18.999
PAGE RIGGS.

01:18.999 --> 01:21.462
HE JUST SAID --
I CAN HEAR.

01:21.462 --> 01:24.295
YOU KNOW THAT DR. HUNT
PUNCHED DR. RIGGS.

01:24.295 --> 01:25.506
THE ONLY WAY THEY'RE GONNA
LEARN TO WORK TOGETHER

01:25.506 --> 01:26.877
IS IF THEY WORK TOGETHER,

01:26.877 --> 01:29.510
SO ANY CARDIO CONSULTS
THAT GET PAGED TO THE PIT,

01:29.510 --> 01:31.382
YOU PAGE RIGGS.

01:31.382 --> 01:34.265
YOU KNOW THIS IS MY ONE
HAPPY PLACE RIGHT NOW?

01:34.265 --> 01:35.806
PLEASE DON'T MAKE IT
A CRAPPY PLACE.

01:35.806 --> 01:37.558
OH, KEPNER.
I FEEL YOU. I DO.

01:37.558 --> 01:38.599
PAGE RIGGS.

01:44.315 --> 01:46.147
HI. MAYA ROBERTS --
DR. KAREV. I KNOW.

01:46.147 --> 01:47.938
UH, THIS IS MY MOM, JUDI.

01:47.938 --> 01:50.070
THANK YOU FOR MAKING THE TIME
TO SEE MY DAUGHTER.

01:50.070 --> 01:51.232
HAVE WE MET BEFORE?

01:51.232 --> 01:52.943
I LOOKED YOU UP.
AND YOU ARE?

01:52.943 --> 01:54.945
UH, CROSS --
DR. CROSS.

01:54.945 --> 01:56.577
GO.
RIGHT.

01:56.577 --> 01:58.118
"MAYA ROBERTS, 15.

01:58.118 --> 02:00.791
STATUS -- POST BELOW-KNEE
AMPUTATION OF THE RIGHT LEG

02:00.791 --> 02:03.204
TWO YEARS AGO AFTER DIAGNOSIS
OF BONE CANCER,

02:03.204 --> 02:04.705
NOW RECURRING IN
THE RIBS AND STERNUM."

02:04.705 --> 02:06.207
I KNOW WHY I'M HERE.

02:06.207 --> 02:08.299
I JUST WANTED
TO TALK ABOUT YOU.

02:08.299 --> 02:10.050
IT SAYS HERE IN YOUR C.V.

02:10.050 --> 02:12.463
YOU MADE BUTTHOLES FOR BABIES
WHO DIDN'T HAVE THEM.

02:12.463 --> 02:13.844
HANG ON. THAT'S --

02:13.844 --> 02:16.307
LISTEN, I'M 15
WITH A CHEST FULL OF CANCER.

02:16.307 --> 02:18.559
THIS HOSPITAL IS KNOWN
FOR MAKING MIRACLES HAPPEN,

02:18.559 --> 02:21.812
AND I'M LOOKING FOR
AN EPIC-SIZE MIRACLE.

02:21.812 --> 02:23.394
ACCORDING TO MY RESEARCH,

02:23.394 --> 02:25.025
IT LOOKS LIKE YOU'RE THE GUY
WHO CAN MAKE IT HAPPEN.

02:26.477 --> 02:27.858
I AM CONFUSED
ABOUT THE BUTTHOLES.

02:27.858 --> 02:29.360
STRANGE DETOUR.
SO, DISCUSS.

02:29.360 --> 02:31.402
OR HOW ABOUT YOU HUMOR ME

02:31.402 --> 02:32.653
AND LET ME PRETEND
LIKE I'M IN CHARGE FOR A SEC?

02:32.653 --> 02:34.445
NOW, UH, MS. ROBERTS --

02:34.445 --> 02:35.656
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO KNOW?

02:35.656 --> 02:38.329
TWO YEARS AGO,
I FELT A PAIN IN MY RIGHT TIBIA.

02:38.329 --> 02:40.331
SHE'S GOT A REAL MIND
FOR THIS STUFF.

02:40.331 --> 02:42.203
THEY DID LABS,
P.E.T. SCAN, THE WORKS.

02:42.203 --> 02:44.955
TURNS OUT I'M ONE IN, LIKE,
A BAJILLION KIDS

02:44.955 --> 02:46.587
TO GET CHONDROSARCOMA.

02:46.587 --> 02:48.168
SO CHEMO AND RADIATION
WEREN'T AN OPTION.

02:48.168 --> 02:49.340
YOU GET POINTS.

02:49.340 --> 02:50.921
SWEET.

02:50.921 --> 02:51.842
HM.

02:51.842 --> 02:53.634
[ SNIFFLES ]
SORRY.

02:53.634 --> 02:55.055
[ SNIFFLES ]

02:55.055 --> 02:56.597
HEY, REMEMBER,
WE SAID NO CRYING.

02:56.597 --> 02:59.640
I KNOW. SORRY.
[ SNIFFLES ]

02:59.640 --> 03:01.432
THERE WAS A ONE IN FOUR CHANCE
OF RECURRENCE,

03:01.432 --> 03:04.184
SO IT'S NOT A HUGE SHOCKER,
BUT IT IS BACK,

03:04.184 --> 03:07.938
AND IT'S BIGGER THAN EVER
IN MY CHEST.

03:10.861 --> 03:12.403
WE HAVE OUR WORK CUT OUT FOR US,
GENTLEMEN.

03:14.074 --> 03:16.447
UH, ROBBINS
IS GOING OUT TONIGHT.

03:16.447 --> 03:18.239
DO YOU WANT TO MAYBE COME OVER
WHEN YOU'RE DONE?

03:18.239 --> 03:19.990
YEAH. NO, CRAP.
WE HAVE A "MER" THING.

03:19.990 --> 03:21.412
AGAIN?
YEAH.

03:21.412 --> 03:23.203
COME OVER AFTER?
YES.

03:23.203 --> 03:25.746
OKAY. GO. FIX YOUR HAIR.

03:27.588 --> 03:29.590
[ SIREN WAILING ]

03:30.961 --> 03:32.713
CHEST PAINS, HUH?
YEP.

03:32.713 --> 03:34.255
SO, WHAT'S HE DOING HERE?
KEPNER, I TOLD YOU --

03:34.255 --> 03:36.507
I KNOW YOU DID,
BUT THIS IS WHAT'S HAPPENING.

03:36.507 --> 03:37.928
I GAVE YOU A DIRECT ORDER.

03:37.928 --> 03:39.139
COME ON, HUNT. YOU'VE TURNED
EVERYONE HERE AGAINST ME.

03:39.139 --> 03:41.011
THE LEAST YOU CAN DO
IS LET ME FRIGGING WORK.

03:41.011 --> 03:42.723
YOU HAVE NO BUSINESS
BEING HERE AT ALL.
GUYS, STOP.

03:42.723 --> 03:44.144
YOU KNOW WHAT? I'M SICK
AND TIRED OF HEARING ABOUT IT.

03:44.144 --> 03:45.606
WHY DON'T FIND
SOMEPLACE ELSE TO WORK?

03:45.606 --> 03:46.937
OH, YAY! SOMEONE'S HURT.
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:46.937 --> 03:49.270
MALE, 55, COMPLAINING
OF TIGHTNESS IN THE CHEST.

03:49.270 --> 03:50.731
SIR, DO YOU HAVE ANY PAIN
IN YOUR LEFT ARM?

03:50.731 --> 03:51.692
NO, NOT REALLY.

03:51.692 --> 03:53.063
MY CHEST HURTS LIKE HELL,
THOUGH.

03:53.063 --> 03:54.114
RIGGS, YOU CAN GO.
I GOT THIS.

03:54.114 --> 03:55.526
CHEST PAINS.
I'LL TAKE IT.

03:55.526 --> 03:57.067
SIR, WHAT DID YOU EAT
THIS MORNING?

03:57.067 --> 03:58.949
A BURRITO --
TWO BURRITOS.

03:58.949 --> 04:01.161
IT'S PROBABLY NOT SURGICAL.
I'LL PAGE SOMEONE IF IT IS.

04:01.161 --> 04:03.364
LET'S GO.
HOW ABOUT YOU LET ME
DO MY JOB?

04:03.364 --> 04:05.125
HOW ABOUT YOU GET
THE HELL AWAY --
HOW ABOUT
YOU BOTH SHUT UP?

04:05.125 --> 04:07.368
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

04:14.545 --> 04:16.337
Meredith: BOOM.
I'LL BE IN, I'LL BE OUT.

04:16.337 --> 04:17.968
THESE SESSIONS SHOULDN'T TAKE
ALL THAT LONG.

04:17.968 --> 04:20.431
BUT BEFORE WE START,
DOCTOR,

04:20.431 --> 04:22.012
I WAS ASSIGNED YOUR CASE,

04:22.012 --> 04:24.264
AND IF YOU WOULD PREFER
A FEMALE THERAPIST,

04:24.264 --> 04:26.186
I WOULD BE TOTALLY
COMFORTABLE WITH THAT.

04:26.186 --> 04:28.098
OH, BECAUSE IT WAS A MAN
WHO ATTACKED ME?

04:28.098 --> 04:30.441
YEAH. AND IT'S IMPORTANT
THAT YOU FEEL

04:30.441 --> 04:32.393
THAT YOU'RE WITH
THE RIGHT PERSON,

04:32.393 --> 04:35.946
THAT YOU FEEL COMFORTABLE,
THAT YOU GET WHAT YOU NEED.

04:35.946 --> 04:37.898
I APPRECIATE THAT.
I'M FINE.

04:37.898 --> 04:39.360
I JUST NEED
A TAPE-AND-GLUE GUY.

04:39.360 --> 04:41.031
TAPE AND GLUE?

04:41.031 --> 04:44.665
YEAH, JUST, YOU KNOW,
ASK ME A FEW QUESTIONS

04:44.665 --> 04:46.166
AND PATCH ME UP
AND SEND ME ON MY WAY.

04:46.166 --> 04:48.208
I'VE BEEN TO THERAPY BEFORE.
UH-HUH.

04:48.208 --> 04:49.460
I'VE DEALT WITH
THE BIG STUFF.

04:49.460 --> 04:51.792
THIS ISN'T THE BIG STUFF
THAT WE'RE DEALING WITH.

04:54.465 --> 04:56.837
MEREDITH...

04:56.837 --> 05:00.130
YOU WERE ATTACKED
IN YOUR OWN HOSPITAL,

05:00.130 --> 05:02.723
AND YOU CONSIDER THAT
SMALL STUFF?

05:03.884 --> 05:05.886
HAVE YOU READ MY FILE?

05:18.819 --> 05:21.532
Therapist: YOU'RE SAYING
THAT YOU'VE BEEN THROUGH A LOT.

05:21.532 --> 05:23.574
I AM, AND I HAVE.
MY MOTHER DIED OF ALZHEIMER'S.

05:23.574 --> 05:26.076
MY STEPMOTHER DIED
OF THE HICCUPS.

05:26.076 --> 05:28.869
MY SISTER DIED
IN A PLANE CRASH.

05:28.869 --> 05:32.873
MY HUSBAND WAS HIT
BY A SEMI.

05:32.873 --> 05:34.755
THAT FILE,
IT'S A REAL PAGE-TURNER.

05:34.755 --> 05:40.461
MEREDITH, SOMETHING TERRIBLE
HAPPENED TO YOU.

05:40.461 --> 05:42.302
IT DID.

05:42.302 --> 05:44.224
AND TERRIBLE THINGS HAPPEN
EVERY DAY.

05:44.224 --> 05:45.676
WAS THE HELL WAS --
April: COMING THROUGH!

05:45.676 --> 05:47.137
OH, MY GOD.

05:47.137 --> 05:48.929
SHEPHERD, WITH ME --
TRAUMA 2.

05:48.929 --> 05:51.432
TAKE HIM INTO TRAUMA 3.

05:51.432 --> 05:53.273
TELL ANY INCOMING
TO GO SOMEWHERE ELSE.

05:53.273 --> 05:55.065
KEEP EVERYONE
OUT OF THE AMBULANCE BAY.

05:55.065 --> 05:57.778
I NEED A TRAUMA PANEL, LAP PADS,
AND A SURGICAL TRAY.

05:57.778 --> 05:59.900
SOMEONE NOTIFY THE O.R.
Woman: RIGHT AWAY, DOCTOR.

05:59.900 --> 06:01.402
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

06:01.402 --> 06:03.033
HOLD ON. YOU'RE NEXT.

06:03.033 --> 06:04.745
I SHOULD'VE GONE
SOMEWHERE ELSE.

06:10.621 --> 06:12.252
WHAT THE HELL WAS THAT?

06:12.252 --> 06:14.044
AMBULANCE EXPLODED.
WHAT?

06:14.044 --> 06:15.836
PARTIAL THICKNESS BURNS
TO THE UPPER CHEST.

06:15.836 --> 06:17.668
FOLLOW THE LIGHT
WITH YOUR EYES.

06:17.668 --> 06:18.709
[ BREATHING SHAKILY ]

06:18.709 --> 06:19.880
OKAY, GOOD.

06:19.880 --> 06:22.092
WHAT HAPPENED?

06:22.092 --> 06:23.634
YOUR RIG EXPLODED,
BUT DON'T WORRY.

06:23.634 --> 06:25.135
WE'VE GOT YOU, OKAY?
YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.

06:25.135 --> 06:27.347
OH, SHEPHERD, THEY NEED YOU
IN TRAUMA 1.

06:27.347 --> 06:28.469
MM-HMM.

06:28.469 --> 06:29.640
THEY FIGURE OUT
WHY THAT RIG BLEW UP?

06:29.640 --> 06:30.931
UH, FIRE DEPARTMENT'S
LOOKING AT IT NOW.

06:30.931 --> 06:33.684
OH, MY GOD.
IT WAS ME.

06:33.684 --> 06:36.567
[ Voice breaking ]
I DIDN'T SECURE THE OXYGEN TANK.

06:36.567 --> 06:39.019
JOHNNY'S ALWAYS SAYING...

06:39.019 --> 06:40.901
HE'S GONNA KILL ME.

06:40.901 --> 06:42.573
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT,
AND HE KNOWS THAT.

06:42.573 --> 06:44.825
HE'S GONNA KILL ME.

06:44.825 --> 06:46.447
[ BREATHING SHAKILY ]

06:46.447 --> 06:48.989
DON'T ARCH YOUR NECK.
ALL RIGHT.

06:48.989 --> 06:51.081
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]
THERE'S A LOT VENOUS BLOOD
IN THE UPPER CHEST.

06:51.081 --> 06:52.743
THE LAC EXTENDS
DEEP INTO THE LIVER.

06:52.743 --> 06:54.455
LET ME GET IN THERE,
ESTABLISH VASCULAR CONTROL.

06:54.455 --> 06:55.956
NO, WE'RE GONNA PACK HIM
AND TAKE HIM UP.

06:55.956 --> 06:57.588
AND THEN WE'LL BE ABLE TO SEE
WHAT THE HELL'S GOING ON.

06:57.588 --> 06:59.039
HE'S OPEN RIGHT NOW.
JUST LET ME WORK.

06:59.039 --> 07:00.380
HE IS HEMORRHAGING
LIKE CRAZY.

07:00.380 --> 07:01.712
I'M NOT GONNA LET HIM
BLEED OUT DOWN HERE.

07:01.712 --> 07:03.544
SUCTION. MORE LAPS.

07:03.544 --> 07:05.596
HE'S GOT A DEPRESSED
SKULL FRACTURE. HE NEEDS A C.T.

07:05.596 --> 07:07.678
LOOK, OWEN, YOU KNOW I CAN DO
THIS. LET ME STABILIZE HIM.

07:07.678 --> 07:09.510
RIGGS, THIS IS THE PLAN.
GET ON BOARD, OR GET OUT.

07:09.510 --> 07:10.641
YOUR PLAN
IS WORKING GREAT.

07:10.641 --> 07:11.762
BETTER STILL,
JUST GET OUT.

07:11.762 --> 07:12.933
KEPNER, OVER HERE.

07:12.933 --> 07:14.605
TO HELL WITH THIS!

07:17.357 --> 07:20.020
WHEN YOU FIRST WOKE UP
AFTER THE ATTACK,

07:20.020 --> 07:22.022
WHAT IS THE FIRST THING
YOU REMEMBER?

07:24.324 --> 07:25.656
PEOPLE.

07:25.656 --> 07:27.067
PEOPLE RUNNING AROUND
EVERYWHERE.

07:27.067 --> 07:28.989
WHO SPECIFICALLY?

07:28.989 --> 07:32.703
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

07:32.703 --> 07:35.786
IT WAS PRETTY CRAZY.

07:35.786 --> 07:37.748
OH. THANK YOU.

07:37.748 --> 07:40.210
UH, YOU, SIR,
HAVE INDIGESTION.

07:40.210 --> 07:42.753
DeLUCA HERE WILL GET YOU
AN ANTACID.

07:42.753 --> 07:45.045
[ CELLPHONE CHIMING ]

07:45.045 --> 07:47.508
SO-- SORRY, SIR.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

07:47.508 --> 07:50.220
AND, UH, ALSO SCHEDULE
AN UPPER ENDOSCOPY, PLEASE.

07:50.220 --> 07:51.852
[ CHIMING CONTINUES ]

07:53.514 --> 07:55.095
DeLUCA,
DO YOU HAVE SOMEWHERE TO BE?
NO.

07:55.095 --> 07:56.517
THEN PUT
THE DAMN PHONE AWAY.

07:56.517 --> 07:57.728
[ CHIMING CONTINUES ]

07:57.728 --> 08:00.190
OKAY, HE'LL, UH, GET YOU
THE REST OF YOUR MEDS,

08:00.190 --> 08:02.733
AND YOU JUST,
UH, SIT TIGHT, OKAY?

08:04.444 --> 08:06.316
[ CHIMING CONTINUES ]

08:09.910 --> 08:11.742
DeLUCA!

08:13.323 --> 08:15.706
TORRES IS ON HER WAY.
OH, OKAY. THANKS.

08:15.706 --> 08:18.378
HEY, UH, LISTEN,
DO YOU THINK

08:18.378 --> 08:20.751
TONIGHT MAYBE YOU AND I
COULD JUST -- I DON'T KNOW.

08:20.751 --> 08:23.754
OH, ACTUALLY, I'M HAVING
SOME PEOPLE OVER TONIGHT.

08:23.754 --> 08:26.336
IT'S -- IT'S NOTHING BIG,
JUST STEPH, BLAKE, AND WARREN.

08:26.336 --> 08:28.298
OKAY, YEAH.
I MEAN, I GET OFF LATE,

08:28.298 --> 08:29.339
BUT I CAN PICK UP SOMETHING
ON THE WAY HOME.

08:29.339 --> 08:31.301
NO, I MEANT, UH,

08:31.301 --> 08:34.474
I'D KIND OF JUST LIKE TO SPEND
SOME TIME WITH MY FRIENDS.

08:34.474 --> 08:36.346
OH.

08:36.346 --> 08:38.559
YEAH, NO.

08:38.559 --> 08:39.980
I GOT SOMETHING LATER ANYWAY,
SO...

08:39.980 --> 08:42.272
OH, GREAT, SO YOU HAVE
SOMEPLACE TO BE.

08:42.272 --> 08:44.855
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH,
I GOT SOMEPLACE TO BE.

08:46.196 --> 08:48.148
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
FINALLY.

08:48.148 --> 08:50.110
UH, CAN YOU, UH,
LOOK AT THESE?

08:50.110 --> 08:51.281
MM-HMM.

08:51.281 --> 08:52.653
SO, HOW OLD
IS THIS PATIENT?

08:52.653 --> 08:55.115
[ SIGHS ]
15 GOING ON 35.

08:55.115 --> 08:56.917
STANDARD TITANIUM PLATES,
RIGHT?

08:56.917 --> 08:58.959
UNLESS HER PARENTS
WILL GO FOR A STEM-CELL
SCAFFOLDING IN THE CHEST.

08:58.959 --> 09:01.291
WELL, IT'S, UH,
JUST THE MOM

09:01.291 --> 09:03.123
AND, LOOK, I-I DON'T WANT
TO LEAVE THIS GIRL

09:03.123 --> 09:04.925
WITH AN UNPROTECTED HEART
FOR YEARS.

09:04.925 --> 09:06.086
I NEED TO MAKE
A RECOMMENDATION.

09:06.086 --> 09:07.467
WELL, WE COULD LOOK
INTO NEW TECHNOLOGY.

09:07.467 --> 09:09.009
NO, I WANT
THE SAFEST OPTION.

09:09.009 --> 09:10.931
THEN YOU GO
WITH PLATES.
TRIED AND TRUE.

09:13.594 --> 09:15.555
[ CELLPHONE CLICKING ]

09:15.555 --> 09:17.437
SO? HIT ME.

09:17.437 --> 09:21.351
WELL, I, UH, CONSULTED WITH
OUR ORTHO AND CARDIO CHIEFS,

09:21.351 --> 09:24.144
AND, UH, THE BEST SOLUTION
IS A TITANIUM-PLATE STERNUM

09:24.144 --> 09:25.145
AND RIBCAGE.

09:25.145 --> 09:27.567
OKAY. THAT'S...

09:27.567 --> 09:28.819
THAT SOUNDS GOOD.

09:28.819 --> 09:30.570
HOW MANY REVISION SURGERIES?

09:30.570 --> 09:34.615
PROBABLY...ONCE A YEAR
UNTIL YOU REACH FULL GROWTH.

09:34.615 --> 09:37.828
AND IF I GET HIT WITH, SAY,
EVEN A NERF BALL TO THE CHEST?

09:37.828 --> 09:40.961
WE'LL -- WE'LL JUST BE
VERY CAREFUL, WON'T WE?

09:40.961 --> 09:42.703
JUST ANSWER MY QUESTION.

09:42.703 --> 09:44.504
IT'S VERY DANGEROUS,
YES.

09:44.504 --> 09:46.376
SO WE'RE TALKING
MULTIPLE SURGERIES?

09:46.376 --> 09:47.968
YOU'RE JUST GONNA OPEN
AND REOPEN MY CHEST?

09:47.968 --> 09:49.670
UM, I'M SORRY.

09:49.670 --> 09:51.421
CAN YOU EXPLAIN
WHAT SHE MEA--

09:51.421 --> 09:54.514
A ZIPPER SCAR.

09:54.514 --> 09:55.766
OH.

09:55.766 --> 09:58.058
OH, H-HONEY, I--

09:58.058 --> 09:59.269
WE'LL NEED TO GO IN
A FEW TIMES,

09:59.269 --> 10:01.521
BUT I ASSURE YOU
IT'S THE SAFEST, BEST OPTION.

10:01.521 --> 10:03.814
I FIGURED OUT HOW TO DO IT ALL
ON A LEG AND A HALF,

10:03.814 --> 10:05.686
AND NOW YOU WANT TO LIMIT
EVERYTHING I DO

10:05.686 --> 10:06.937
FOR MY ENTIRE CHILDHOOD?

10:06.937 --> 10:09.529
THIS IS HOW YOU GET
THE REST OF YOUR CHILDHOOD.

10:09.529 --> 10:11.031
I'M TRYING TO SAVE
YOUR LIFE, MAYA.

10:11.031 --> 10:12.903
SWEETHEART,
WE SHOULD CONSIDER THIS.

10:12.903 --> 10:15.946
MAYBE --
I WENT TO THREE DIFFERENT
HOSPITALS BEFORE I CAME HERE,

10:15.946 --> 10:17.287
AND THEY ALL SAID
THE SAME THING.

10:17.287 --> 10:19.870
THEY SAID, "GO TO GREY-SLOAN.
DO TO DR. KAREV."

10:19.870 --> 10:23.123
SO NOW I'M HERE, AND THIS IS
ALL I GET -- JUST THIS?

10:23.123 --> 10:24.795
I'M DISAPPOINTED IN YOU.

10:24.795 --> 10:27.417
DR. KAREV,
YOU'RE OFF MY CASE.

10:27.417 --> 10:28.749
I'M SORRY?

10:28.749 --> 10:29.880
YOU'RE FIRED.

10:32.673 --> 10:34.634
Meredith:
A TERRIBLE THING HAPPENED.

10:34.634 --> 10:36.807
I DID GET KNOCKED AROUND.

10:36.807 --> 10:38.308
BUT NOBODY DIED.

10:42.562 --> 10:46.396
AND ANY DAY WHERE NOBODY DIES,
THAT'S A GOOD DAY.

10:52.072 --> 10:53.694
SO, WHEN YOU WERE LAID UP,
HEALING,

10:53.694 --> 10:55.115
WHO VISITED YOU THE MOST?
ALEX.

10:55.115 --> 10:56.777
REMIND ME -- ALEX IS...

10:56.777 --> 10:59.409
ALEX IS THE ONE WHO PROPOSED
TO HIS GIRLFRIEND.

10:59.409 --> 11:00.951
RIGHT.
AND SHE SAID NO.

11:00.951 --> 11:02.372
WELL, SEE,
SHE DIDN'T REALLY SAY NO,

11:02.372 --> 11:04.374
AND SHE DIDN'T SAY YES,
AND THEN SHE BOOTED HIM,

11:04.374 --> 11:06.586
AND THEN HE CAME BACK
TO LIVE WITH ME.

11:06.586 --> 11:09.049
ALEX WAS THERE
WHEN YOU WOKE UP.

11:09.049 --> 11:12.753
I DELIVERED HIM
ON A SILVER PLATTER TO HER.

11:12.753 --> 11:14.174
AND HE STILL MANAGED
TO SCREW IT UP. UGH.

11:14.174 --> 11:15.595
YOU SAID HE MOVED BACK IN
WITH HER.

11:15.595 --> 11:17.097
I MEAN TO THE PLACE.

11:17.097 --> 11:18.388
THEY'RE TOGETHER,
BUT THEY'RE NOT TOGETHER,

11:18.388 --> 11:19.639
BUT THEY COULD BE TOGETHER.

11:19.639 --> 11:22.262
IT'S...
THEY'RE STUPID.
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:22.262 --> 11:24.104
YOU HAVE FEELINGS FOR ALEX?
ARE YOU IN LOVE WITH ALEX?

11:24.104 --> 11:25.896
[ Laughing ]
DO I HAVE FEELINGS FOR ALEX?

11:25.896 --> 11:27.017
[ CHUCKLES ]
THAT'S FUNNY.

11:27.017 --> 11:28.268
[ LAUGHS ] NO.

11:28.268 --> 11:29.770
[ CHUCKLES ] I'M SORRY.

11:29.770 --> 11:33.023
I'M JUST TRYING TO UNDERSTAND
WHY WE'RE TALKING ABOUT THEM.

11:33.023 --> 11:37.117
BECAUSE HE'S BEING STUPID.

11:38.238 --> 11:40.450
UH, CAN SHE ACTUALLY FIRE US?
SHE'S A KID.

11:40.450 --> 11:41.701
OH, SHUT UP.

11:41.701 --> 11:43.784
SHE'S OLDER THAN YOU ARE,
AND SHE'S SMARTER.

11:43.784 --> 11:45.826
SHE'LL COOL OFF.
SHE'LL COME AROUND.

11:45.826 --> 11:47.037
GO CHECK MY POST-OPS.

11:47.037 --> 11:49.129
WELL,
I'VE NEVER BEEN FIRED BEFORE.

11:49.129 --> 11:51.331
DOES THIS GO
ON MY PERMANENT RECORD?!

11:51.331 --> 11:52.632
GOD.

11:54.755 --> 11:57.337
YOU -- YOU HAVE TO STOP
PAGING ME, OKAY?

11:57.337 --> 11:59.009
I'M GETTING IN TROUBLE NOW.
I WAS TRYING TO FIND OUT
IF YOU WERE --

11:59.009 --> 12:00.390
"YOU OKAY? ARE YOU OKAY?
ARE YOU OKAY?"

12:00.390 --> 12:02.392
YES, I'M OKAY.
WHY WOULDN'T I BE OKAY?

12:02.392 --> 12:04.344
I THOUGHT YOU GOT BLOWN UP
BY AN AMBULANCE.

12:04.344 --> 12:05.936
WHAT? I WASN'T EVEN...

12:07.347 --> 12:09.189
YOU WERE WORRIED ABOUT ME.

12:11.942 --> 12:13.233
AWW.

12:15.445 --> 12:16.526
[ CELLPHONE CHIMING ]

12:16.526 --> 12:18.738
OH. CRAP.

12:18.738 --> 12:20.030
A CONSULT.

12:20.030 --> 12:21.121
MNH-MNH.

12:21.121 --> 12:22.452
MM, OKAY.

12:22.452 --> 12:23.914
NOW YOU'RE GETTING ME
IN TROUBLE.

12:25.575 --> 12:27.457
[ SIGHS ]

12:27.457 --> 12:28.538
[ SIGHS ]

12:28.538 --> 12:29.669
MM.

12:32.332 --> 12:34.004
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

12:34.965 --> 12:36.256
[ DOOR OPENS ]

12:36.256 --> 12:39.179
I MEAN, WHO CARES
IF DeLUCA IS AN INTERN?

12:39.179 --> 12:41.641
IT'S ALL SEXY AND SECRET
AT FIRST,

12:41.641 --> 12:43.934
AND THEN IT'S JUST
A PAIN IN THE ASS.

12:43.934 --> 12:45.725
SO THEY SHOULD JUST
BRING IT OUT IN THE OPEN.

12:45.725 --> 12:46.847
THAT'S WHAT DEREK AND I DID,

12:46.847 --> 12:48.889
AND WE HAVE THREE
BEAUTIFUL CHILDREN.

12:48.889 --> 12:50.891
UH, IS MAGGIE THE ONE IN AA?

12:50.891 --> 12:52.652
OR IS SHE THE HOVERER?

12:52.652 --> 12:55.065
THE HOVERER.
THAT'S THE OTHER THING.

12:55.065 --> 12:57.527
IF SHE WAS GETTING IT
REGULAR,

12:57.527 --> 13:00.240
MAYBE SHE WOULD STOP HOVERING
ALL THE TIME.

13:00.240 --> 13:02.903
[ INDISTINCT TALKING
ON P.A. SYSTEM ]

13:02.903 --> 13:03.864
OH! SORRY.
HEY.

13:04.905 --> 13:07.617
UM...HOW ARE YOU?

13:07.617 --> 13:09.329
ARE YOU --
ARE YOU GOOD?

13:11.121 --> 13:12.672
DID YOU HEAR
ABOUT THE AMBULANCE?

13:12.672 --> 13:13.834
OH, YEAH, I KNOW.

13:13.834 --> 13:15.675
THAT'S SO CRAZY, RIGHT?

13:15.675 --> 13:19.219
WELL, I MEAN, FIRE, O2 TANKS,
POOR MAINTENANCE, CIGARETTES.

13:19.219 --> 13:22.382
I'M SORRY.
UH, UH, REASONS.

13:22.382 --> 13:23.884
AMBULANCES EXPLODE.

13:23.884 --> 13:25.926
IT HAPPENS ALL THE TIME,
ACTUALLY, WHICH IS WEIRD,

13:25.926 --> 13:28.518
CONSIDERING THAT THEIR JOB IS
TO NOT KILL PEOPLE BUT...

13:28.518 --> 13:29.689
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

13:29.689 --> 13:32.142
IT HAPPENS JUST LIKE
[IMITATES EXPLOSION]

13:33.643 --> 13:36.897
YEAH, SO, UM...

13:36.897 --> 13:38.028
ARE YOU GOOD?

13:38.028 --> 13:39.779
I'M OKAY.

13:39.779 --> 13:41.992
UH, I SHOULD...

13:43.743 --> 13:46.576
I DIDN'T SCREW THEM UP.
I WAS NICE.

13:46.576 --> 13:48.078
PENNY KILLED MY HUSBAND.

13:48.078 --> 13:50.370
I TOOK HER IN,
I'M TEACHING HER.

13:50.370 --> 13:52.372
I AM TRYING TO MAKE
SOMETHING GOOD OUT OF IT.

13:52.372 --> 13:54.544
THAT WAS VERY COOL OF ME.
I DIDN'T HAVE TO DO THAT.

13:54.544 --> 13:56.756
NO, YOU DIDN'T,
BUT WHY DID YOU?

13:56.756 --> 13:59.299
AND NOW CALLIE THINKS
I'M COMING BETWEEN THEM,

13:59.299 --> 14:01.051
AND BLAKE THINKS SO, TOO.
I CAN FEEL IT.

14:01.051 --> 14:02.462
AND IT'S JUST NOT TRUE.

14:02.462 --> 14:06.136
I DID NOT COME BETWEEN
THEIR GREAT LOVE -- WASN'T ME.

14:07.517 --> 14:10.350
I'M SORRY.
WHO'S CALLIE AGAIN?

14:10.350 --> 14:12.562
CALLIE IS MY FRIEND
IN ORTHO.
AH.

14:12.562 --> 14:13.894
COME ON. KEEP UP.

14:13.894 --> 14:15.605
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

14:15.605 --> 14:17.187
ICP IS NORMALIZING.

14:17.187 --> 14:18.608
THIS DRAIN
IS DOING THE TRICK.

14:18.608 --> 14:19.649
WE'LL OBSERVE HIM TONIGHT,

14:19.649 --> 14:21.241
AND I'LL TAKE HIM UP
TO THE O.R. TOMORROW

14:21.241 --> 14:22.692
AND REPAIR THE LIVER LAC.

14:22.692 --> 14:24.074
KEPNER, YOU FREE?
UH, YEAH.
JUST LET ME KNOW.

14:24.074 --> 14:25.485
GREAT. I'LL GO SCRUB IN

14:25.485 --> 14:26.786
AND REMOVE THE DRAIN
AT THE SAME TIME.

14:26.786 --> 14:28.038
MM-HMM.

14:30.700 --> 14:32.752
SO, YOU STILL LIVING
WITH RICHARD?

14:32.752 --> 14:35.375
I'M CRASHING HERE.
IT'S A BETTER COMMUTE.

14:35.375 --> 14:38.418
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:38.418 --> 14:40.590
AMELIA...

14:40.590 --> 14:41.591
YOU KNOW
YOU CAN STAY WITH ME.

14:41.591 --> 14:44.554
IT'S NOT A GOOD IDEA
FOR MY SOBRIETY.

14:44.554 --> 14:45.675
RIGHT.

14:47.467 --> 14:48.508
I'M GONNA NEED DINNER,
THOUGH.

14:48.508 --> 14:50.510
GREAT.

14:50.510 --> 14:52.142
DINNER TONIGHT?

14:52.142 --> 14:54.014
OKAY.

14:56.186 --> 14:57.777
SO, HUNT AND I WILL DO
THE LIVER LAC TOMORROW.

14:57.777 --> 14:59.019
HOW IS THE, UH, PARTNER?

14:59.019 --> 15:01.942
STABLE.
WORRIED ABOUT HIS FRIEND.

15:01.942 --> 15:04.154
YOU SHOULD HAVE CARDIO THERE,
TOO,

15:04.154 --> 15:05.615
SO BRING IN RIGGS
JUST TO BE SAFE.

15:05.615 --> 15:06.786
[ SIGHS ] COME ON.

15:06.786 --> 15:08.578
I'M SORRY?

15:08.578 --> 15:11.911
YOU KNOW THERE WAS AN EXPLOSION
IN THE E.R. THIS MORNING.

15:11.911 --> 15:14.034
I JUST REALLY DON'T WANT TO SEE
ANOTHER ONE

15:14.034 --> 15:15.665
OVER AN OPEN PATIENT.

15:15.665 --> 15:17.297
YOU MAKE A GOOD POINT.

15:20.210 --> 15:21.671
[ SIGHS ]

15:21.671 --> 15:23.803
WAIT -- SO IT ALL COMES OUT
IN ONE PIECE?
EXACTLY.

15:23.803 --> 15:25.595
THAT'S SO FREAKING COOL.

15:25.595 --> 15:26.967
[ LAUGHTER ]

15:26.967 --> 15:28.508
WHAT'S GOING ON?

15:28.508 --> 15:31.181
OH, UM, DR. KAREV, UH, THESE TWO
ARE GONNA MAKE ME THOSE.

15:31.181 --> 15:32.722
PIERCE AND I HAD AN IDEA.

15:32.722 --> 15:34.354
'CAUSE THEY'RE GENIUSES.

15:34.354 --> 15:35.815
WELL, SHE KIND OF IS, TOO.

15:35.815 --> 15:39.019
IT DOES SOUND
PRETTY AMAZING.

15:39.019 --> 15:40.520
YOU JUST TOOK OVER
MY CASE?

15:40.520 --> 15:43.403
SHE PAGED US
FOR A CONSULT.

15:43.403 --> 15:47.327
YEAH, NO OFFENSE, BUT YOU'RE
NOT MY DOCTOR ANYMORE.

15:47.327 --> 15:50.490
BUT I THINK WHEN YOU SEE THIS,
YOU'RE GONNA WANT IN.

15:50.490 --> 15:52.492
CAN YOU SHOW HIM THIS?
YEAH, HIT IT.

15:52.492 --> 15:54.494
Callie: OKAY, SO, I CAN EXCISE
MAYA'S TUMORS,

15:54.494 --> 15:56.706
BUT INSTEAD OF THE TRADITIONAL
TITANIUM RECONSTRUCTION,

15:56.706 --> 15:58.788
I CAN 3-D PRINT
A NEW STERNUM AND RIBS.

15:58.788 --> 16:00.840
THEY'LL BE MOLDED TO HER
EXACT BODY SPECIFICATIONS

16:00.840 --> 16:03.343
SO SHE CAN MOVE AROUND
MORE NATURALLY.

16:03.343 --> 16:04.884
HAVE YOU EVER DONE THIS?
IT'S ONLY BEEN DONE ONCE BEFORE
ON AN ADULT,

16:04.884 --> 16:05.795
BUT I CAN MODIFY IT
FOR A CHILD.

16:05.795 --> 16:08.008
YEAH, I'LL BE THE FIRST.

16:08.008 --> 16:09.639
I'LL LOOK LIKE THE TERMINATOR,
WHICH IS BADASS.

16:09.639 --> 16:11.511
[ LAUGHTER ]

16:11.511 --> 16:13.393
CAN I SEE YOU TWO
OUTSIDE?

16:13.393 --> 16:16.646
YOU SAID YOURSELF TITANIUM
PLATES ARE THE BEST OPTION.

16:16.646 --> 16:17.767
THAT WAS BEFORE I KNEW

16:17.767 --> 16:20.270
THAT CALLIE COULD PRINT HER
HER OWN RIBCAGE.

16:20.270 --> 16:22.482
IT WILL BE FEWER SURGERIES
IN THE LONG RUN.

16:22.482 --> 16:24.314
YOU'RE NOT EXPERIMENTING
ON SOME KID.

16:24.314 --> 16:25.905
SHE MAY THINK SHE KNOWS
WHAT SHE WANTS,

16:25.905 --> 16:27.447
BUT SHE'S NOT OLD ENOUGH
TO UNDERSTAND THE RISKS.

16:27.447 --> 16:29.779
SHE GETS IT.
TRUST ME.

16:29.779 --> 16:31.491
I KNOW A LITTLE SOMETHING
ABOUT BEING LABELED

16:31.491 --> 16:32.952
TOO SMART FOR YOUR AGE.

16:32.952 --> 16:34.614
I LOVE HER.

16:34.614 --> 16:36.076
I'M NOT SIGNING OFF
ON THIS.

16:36.076 --> 16:37.827
YOU'RE NOT ON THE CASE
ANYMORE,

16:37.827 --> 16:39.539
AND HER MOM HAS
THE CONSENT FORMS.

16:39.539 --> 16:41.381
OH, YOU KNOW AS WELL AS I DO
SHE'S FREAKING USELESS.

16:41.381 --> 16:43.963
I MEAN, YOU CAN'T EVEN --
KAREV, KAREV.

16:45.385 --> 16:47.627
[ SIGHS ]

16:47.627 --> 16:49.589
MS. ROBERTS, PLEASE.

16:49.589 --> 16:51.681
THIS IS A-A DANGEROUS
EXPERIMENTAL PROCEDURE

16:51.681 --> 16:55.725
WITH ZERO PROOF THAT IT'LL WORK,
LET ALONE KEEP YOUR KID ALIVE.

16:55.725 --> 16:58.188
TRUST ME WHEN I TELL YOU
YOU DON'T WANT TO DO THIS.

17:02.021 --> 17:03.643
PLEASE, MOM.

17:03.643 --> 17:06.446
IT'S WHAT SHE WANTS.

17:06.446 --> 17:08.698
♪♪

17:17.707 --> 17:19.499
YOU SWIPED HER.

17:19.499 --> 17:21.000
WE DIDN'T SWIPE HER.

17:21.000 --> 17:22.162
SHE FIRED YOU
AND ASKED US.

17:22.162 --> 17:23.793
NO ONE'S LOOKING OUT
FOR THIS KID --

17:23.793 --> 17:25.625
NOT HER MOM,
NOT -- NOT ANYONE.
UM, WE ARE, ALEX.

17:25.625 --> 17:27.877
AND I WOULDN'T HAVE
EVEN SUGGESTED IT

17:27.877 --> 17:29.929
IF I DIDN'T BELIEVE THAT
IT WAS THE BEST THING FOR HER.
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
NO ARGUING.

17:29.929 --> 17:31.801
FUN. REMEMBER? FUN?

17:31.801 --> 17:33.973
FOR MEREDITH,
FOR SUPPORT.

17:33.973 --> 17:35.595
I POSTPONED SEX FOR THIS.

17:35.595 --> 17:36.596
Therapist:
MAGGIE'S A HOVERER.

17:36.596 --> 17:37.677
GOD,
SHE HOVERS ALL THE TIME.

17:37.677 --> 17:39.679
DOES IT BOTHER YOU,
THE HOVERING?

17:39.679 --> 17:41.811
NO, SHE'S JUST BEING SISTERLY
OR WHATEVER.

17:41.811 --> 17:43.103
WHY WOULD YOU SAY THAT?

17:43.103 --> 17:44.644
SO, HOW LONG IS THIS
GOING TO LAST?

17:44.644 --> 17:45.775
COME ON. IT'S FUN.

17:45.775 --> 17:47.066
I WANT TO GO TO BED.

17:47.066 --> 17:48.858
OH, I DO, TOO,
AND I CAN'T GO HOME.

17:48.858 --> 17:50.990
I DON'T WANT TO GO HOME --
ALONE.

17:50.990 --> 17:52.902
[ SIGHS ] I MISS PENNY.
I MISS HAVING SEX.

17:52.902 --> 17:55.155
UGH. PENNY AND I
HAD THE GREATEST SEX.

17:55.155 --> 17:57.117
[ Chuckling ] IT WAS THAT
"JOURNEY OF DISCOVERY" GREAT SEX

17:57.117 --> 17:58.198
YOU HAVE IN THE BEGINNING.

17:58.198 --> 17:59.749
JO AND I HAD SEX LIKE THAT
ALL THE TIME.

17:59.749 --> 18:01.701
AND NOW NO PENNY, NO SEX.

18:01.701 --> 18:03.663
NO SEX WITH PENNY.
NONE OF IT.

18:03.663 --> 18:06.336
OKAY, LET'S NOT TALK ABOUT SEX,
BECAUSE THE CHIEF IS HERE.

18:06.336 --> 18:07.757
Bailey: I'M JUST
EATING MY PIZZA.

18:07.757 --> 18:10.089
BESIDES, IT SOUNDS LIKE NONE
OF Y'ALL ARE GETTING ANY ANYWAY.

18:10.089 --> 18:12.382
PIERCE IS GETTING SOME.
NO, I'M NOT. DON'T SAY THAT.
FORGET HE SAID THAT.

18:12.382 --> 18:13.633
SO ANNOYING.

18:13.633 --> 18:15.975
SHE HAS PEOPLE OVER
ALL THE TIME,

18:15.975 --> 18:17.927
LIKE IF I'M ALONE,
I'LL EXPLODE OR SOMETHING.

18:17.927 --> 18:19.479
THEY WON'T GO AWAY.

18:19.479 --> 18:20.930
OKAY, BUT, GUYS, REALLY,
YOU CAN GO.

18:20.930 --> 18:22.812
NO, WE'RE HERE
BECAUSE IT'S FUN.

18:22.812 --> 18:25.525
NO, REALLY, IT'S OKAY.
I CAN --
ARE YOU SURE?
'CAUSE YOU SEEM A LITTLE --

18:25.525 --> 18:27.106
CRANKY AS HELL?
WHICH IS TOTALLY
UNDERSTANDABLE

18:27.106 --> 18:28.648
WITH EVERYTHING
YOU'VE GONE THROUGH.

18:28.648 --> 18:30.150
OF COURSE YOU WOULD BE.
Callie:
AND WE'RE WORRIED.

18:30.150 --> 18:31.651
YOU DON'T HAVE TO WORRY.
WE KNOW.

18:31.651 --> 18:33.733
AND I'M NOT CRANKY.
I KNOW.

18:33.733 --> 18:36.196
EXCEPT YOU ARE
ALL THE TIME.
[ SIGHS ]

18:36.196 --> 18:37.327
Therapist:
DO YOU WANT TO BE ALONE?

18:37.327 --> 18:39.579
WELL, I'M A WIDOW.

18:39.579 --> 18:40.620
I'M GOOD AT IT.

18:40.620 --> 18:42.242
I REALLY JUST WANT --
WHAT?

18:42.242 --> 18:43.373
WELL, THEN,
TELL THEM TO GO AWAY.

18:43.373 --> 18:45.245
WELL, NO, BECAUSE THEY'RE
JUST TRYING TO HELP.

18:45.245 --> 18:47.046
WHAT DO YOU WANT?
WHAT CAN WE DO?

18:47.046 --> 18:48.668
Therapist:
BUT THEY'RE NOT BEING HELPFUL.

18:48.668 --> 18:51.671
AND IT'S ALL RIGHT
FOR YOU TO TELL THEM THAT.

18:52.632 --> 18:54.674
LEAVE MY HOUSE.

18:54.674 --> 18:56.256
GET OUT.

18:56.256 --> 18:58.678
I MEAN, THANK YOU, BUT,
REALLY, JUST GO BE WITH WHOEVER

18:58.678 --> 19:01.100
SOMEWHERE ELSE
SO THAT I CAN GO TO SLEEP.

19:04.354 --> 19:05.104
LEAVE.

19:07.397 --> 19:09.269
YOU SEEM ANGRY.

19:09.269 --> 19:11.481
I'M NOT.

19:11.481 --> 19:13.693
MY BAD.

19:13.693 --> 19:15.655
I TOOK YOUR ADVICE.

19:15.655 --> 19:17.827
I KICKED THEM ALL
OUT OF MY HOUSE LAST NIGHT.

19:17.827 --> 19:20.159
AND...

19:20.159 --> 19:21.951
IT WORKED.
THEY LEFT ME ALONE.

19:21.951 --> 19:23.243
WELL,
THAT'S WHAT YOU WANTED.

19:23.243 --> 19:25.585
I KNOW.

19:32.752 --> 19:34.344
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]
HEY. DR. WEBBER.

19:34.344 --> 19:35.505
ARIZONA'S JUST GONNA BE
A SECOND, SO --

19:35.505 --> 19:37.257
OH, THANKS.

19:37.257 --> 19:38.968
HEY,
LET'S GET A MOVE ON!

19:38.968 --> 19:40.430
TRIVIA'S STARTING
IN 15 MINUTES!

19:40.430 --> 19:41.511
Arizona: COMING!

19:41.511 --> 19:43.473
YEAH.
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:43.473 --> 19:45.144
HEY.
LOOKING SHARP.

19:45.144 --> 19:46.145
GOT A HOT DATE?

19:46.145 --> 19:47.397
UH, YEAH,
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

19:47.397 --> 19:48.728
HMM.

19:48.728 --> 19:50.770
SHE'S, UH --
WE'RE KIND OF KEEPING IT QUIET.

19:50.770 --> 19:54.073
OH. SECRET ROMANCE?

19:54.073 --> 19:56.526
I'M GUESSING
SHE WORKS AT THE HOSPITAL?

19:56.526 --> 19:59.319
I MEAN, SHE --

19:59.319 --> 20:01.451
[ Chuckling ] RELAX, SON.
[ Chuckling ] OKAY.

20:01.451 --> 20:03.082
I GET IT.

20:03.082 --> 20:04.284
YOU KNOW,
IT'S BEEN A FEW YEARS,

20:04.284 --> 20:06.706
BUT IF YOURS IS ANYTHING
LIKE MINE WAS,

20:06.706 --> 20:09.629
KEEPING IT A SECRET MAKES IT
JUST THAT MUCH MORE EXCITING.

20:09.629 --> 20:11.631
YOU KNOW,
YOU'RE TOTALLY RIGHT.

20:11.631 --> 20:13.923
I MEAN, SHE --
SHE KEEPS IT SO TOGETHER

20:13.923 --> 20:16.135
IN FRONT OF PEOPLE AT WORK,
BUT THEN, WHEN WE'RE ALONE,

20:16.135 --> 20:17.547
SHE'S SO --
SHE'S A WILDCAT, HUH?

20:17.547 --> 20:19.889
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

20:19.889 --> 20:22.642
HOW...DO I LOOK?

20:22.642 --> 20:23.643
DO I LOOK HOT?

20:23.643 --> 20:24.974
[ STAMMERS ]
YOU'RE VERY HOT.

20:24.974 --> 20:27.477
CAN WE GO NOW?
[ LAUGHS ]

20:27.477 --> 20:29.849
THANK YOU. WHEW!

20:29.849 --> 20:31.351
OKAY. SEE YOU LATER.

20:31.351 --> 20:32.982
YOU HAVE FUN, TOO.
HAVE FUN TONIGHT, DeLUCA.

20:32.982 --> 20:34.314
THANKS.

20:34.314 --> 20:37.527
OH, AND, UH...
YOU CAN'T TAME A WILDCAT.

20:37.527 --> 20:39.819
[ CAR ALARM CHIRPS ]

20:39.819 --> 20:42.622
IT'S INFURIATING BECAUSE
I KNOW THAT OUR PROBLEMS

20:42.622 --> 20:44.324
HAVEN'T JUST
MAGICALLY DISAPPEARED.

20:44.324 --> 20:45.915
THANKS.
MM-HMM.

20:45.915 --> 20:47.457
HEY, UH, WHEN ARE THE REST
OF THE GUYS COMING?

20:48.668 --> 20:49.829
THIS IS IT.

20:51.000 --> 20:52.792
ALL RIGHT.
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

20:52.792 --> 20:54.213
Penny:
WHY DID YOU LET HIM MOVE IN?

20:54.213 --> 20:56.836
BECAUSE HE SHOWED UP
ON MY DOOR ALL SAD

20:56.836 --> 20:58.758
WITH HIS BIG, SWEET FACE

20:58.758 --> 21:00.970
AND MADE ME FORGET EVERYTHING
THAT WAS WRONG WITH US.

21:00.970 --> 21:02.302
I KNOW.

21:02.302 --> 21:03.683
I SEE CALLIE WALKING DOWN
THE HALL,

21:03.683 --> 21:06.936
SHE AND I ARE BARELY TALKING,
AND I STILL GET STUPID.

21:06.936 --> 21:08.187
UGH.

21:08.187 --> 21:09.519
I WANT TO GET STUPID
OVER SOMEBODY.

21:09.519 --> 21:11.270
ALL I EVER FEEL IS SMART.

21:11.270 --> 21:14.394
I JUST WANT TO TAKE
HIS DUMB, GORGEOUS FACE,

21:14.394 --> 21:17.196
AND I JUST -- I WANT TO --
I WANT TO PUMMEL IT...

21:17.196 --> 21:22.071
AND KISS IT AND MARRY IT
AND JUST PUMMEL IT.

21:22.071 --> 21:24.113
Penny: I GET THAT, TOO.
MM.

21:24.113 --> 21:26.536
NOT THE PUMMELING,
BUT THE KISSING.
MM.

21:26.536 --> 21:28.578
I THOUGHT YOU DIDN'T EVEN
WANT TO MARRY HIM?

21:28.578 --> 21:31.040
I DON'T KNOW WHAT I WANT.
I CAN'T BE TRUSTED.

21:31.040 --> 21:33.583
I WANT TO KNOW
WHAT GUYS WANT.

21:33.583 --> 21:35.044
HEY, WARREN, WARREN.

21:35.044 --> 21:36.506
YOU'RE A GUY.
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

21:36.506 --> 21:41.130
UM...YOU KNOW, THAT'S, UH --
THAT'S -- THAT'S TOUGH. UM...

21:41.130 --> 21:43.763
DID ANYBODY SEE THAT
AN AMBULANCE BLEW UP
IN THE E.R. TODAY?

21:43.763 --> 21:47.186
NO, WE'RE SERIOUS.
WHAT DO GUYS WANT?

21:47.186 --> 21:49.228
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT DO GUYS WANT?

21:49.228 --> 21:52.191
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
OUT OF THIS CONVERSATION.

21:52.191 --> 21:53.142
[ LAUGHTER ]
[ CELLPHONE CHIMING ]

21:53.142 --> 21:55.695
OH, UM...

21:55.695 --> 21:58.277
I JUST GOT AN IMPORTANT TEXT,
AND I HAVE TO GO.
OH.

21:58.277 --> 22:00.530
YOU ARE IMPOSSIBLE.

22:00.530 --> 22:03.823
OH, WOMEN ARE JUST
AS IMPOSSIBLE.
REALLY?

22:03.823 --> 22:07.246
LOOK, I, UH --
I CAN'T SPEAK FOR ALL MEN.

22:07.246 --> 22:11.621
I'M JUST A GUY WHO WANTS
TO GO HOME TO HIS WIFE.

22:11.621 --> 22:13.453
SORRY. GOOD NIGHT.

22:13.453 --> 22:16.626
[ CHUCKLES ]
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

22:16.626 --> 22:17.757
SCREW BAILEY.

22:17.757 --> 22:19.839
[ BOTH LAUGH ]
AW.

22:19.839 --> 22:21.300
SHE GOT THE GOOD ONE.

22:21.300 --> 22:24.053
SHE DID. MM.

22:24.053 --> 22:26.766
[ GASPS ]
HO HO!

22:26.766 --> 22:28.057
LOOKS LIKE YOU OWE ME
ANOTHER BEER.

22:28.057 --> 22:30.179
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]
OH, HELL.

22:30.179 --> 22:33.142
HEY, NO ONE FORCED YOU TO
TAKE BETS YOU COULDN'T WIN.

22:34.434 --> 22:35.895
WHAT IS THE DEAL,
NATHAN?

22:37.437 --> 22:39.479
NO DEAL.

22:39.479 --> 22:41.320
GO AGAIN?

22:41.320 --> 22:43.743
I TALKED ABOUT OWEN
DOZENS OF TIMES

22:43.743 --> 22:44.984
WHEN WE WERE OVER THERE,

22:44.984 --> 22:46.155
AND YOU NEVER EVEN MENTIONED
KNOWING HIM.

22:46.155 --> 22:48.748
WELL, I DIDN'T WANT
TO TALK ABOUT IT.

22:48.748 --> 22:50.950
SO, WHAT, YOU GUYS HAVE JUST,
LIKE, ALWAYS HATED EACH OTHER?

22:50.950 --> 22:53.202
NO, I NEVER HATED HIM.

22:53.202 --> 22:57.336
WE BECAME DOCTORS TOGETHER, WENT
THROUGH SCHOOL, FIELD TRAINING.

22:57.336 --> 22:59.709
THERE WAS NO ONE I TRUSTED MORE.
WE WERE LIKE BROTHERS.

22:59.709 --> 23:00.880
WHAT HAPPENED?

23:02.672 --> 23:04.303
YOU'RE UP.

23:04.303 --> 23:05.925
OKAY, SO WE'RE NOT TALKING
ABOUT THIS?

23:05.925 --> 23:07.557
WE'RE PLAYING DARTS.

23:12.642 --> 23:14.063
HOW'D YOU GET SO GOOD
AT DARTS ANYWAY?

23:16.105 --> 23:19.979
YOU PICK UP SOME THINGS WHEN
YOU HAVE NO REASON TO GO HOME.

23:19.979 --> 23:22.482
SO, WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

23:22.482 --> 23:23.613
YOU GONNA SIGN THE PAPERS?

23:25.525 --> 23:26.826
WE'RE PLAYING DARTS.

23:30.740 --> 23:32.952
FINE WITH ME.

23:32.952 --> 23:35.164
HEY, YOU READY?
I'M STARVING.

23:35.164 --> 23:36.335
LISTEN, CAN WE DO THIS
ANOTHER NIGHT?

23:36.335 --> 23:37.877
[ SIGHS ]

23:37.877 --> 23:39.168
UH, OKAY.

23:39.168 --> 23:41.090
I'M NOT HUNGRY,
AND I-I DON'T WANT TO --

23:41.090 --> 23:42.131
WHAT'S WRONG?
NOTHING, NOTHING.

23:42.131 --> 23:44.173
JUST BE BETTER ANOTHER NIGHT,
OKAY?

23:44.173 --> 23:45.214
IS THIS ABOUT RIGGS?

23:45.214 --> 23:46.636
CAN YOU...

23:46.636 --> 23:49.178
I'M NOT GETTING INTO IT.

23:49.178 --> 23:50.890
EVERYTHING DOESN'T NEED
TO BE TALKED ABOUT.

23:50.890 --> 23:53.643
OKAY.

23:53.643 --> 23:55.394
YEAH, I UNDERSTAND.

23:55.394 --> 23:59.398
SO ANOTHER TIME YOU WILL
CALL ME, AND WE'LL GO OUT.

23:59.398 --> 24:02.822
BUT YOU WON'T, WILL YOU?

24:02.822 --> 24:05.064
OR YOU WILL
AND I WILL CAVE AND GO

24:05.064 --> 24:08.027
AND I WILL TALK TOO MUCH
AND YOU WILL SAY NOTHING.

24:08.027 --> 24:11.531
AND I-I'M -- I DON'T KNOW HOW
TO DO THIS THING THAT YOU DO

24:11.531 --> 24:13.743
WHERE YOU MAKE ME
FEEL LIKE CRAP

24:13.743 --> 24:15.705
AND THERE ARE NO WORDS
COMING OUT OF YOUR MOUTH.

24:15.705 --> 24:17.957
SO...WHATEVER.

24:17.957 --> 24:21.000
YOU'LL CALL ME MAYBE --
OR MAYBE NOT.

24:21.000 --> 24:24.173
AND MAYBE I WILL NOT CARE.

24:28.467 --> 24:29.799
I HAD A SISTER.

24:33.392 --> 24:35.224
MEGAN.

24:35.224 --> 24:37.056
SHE WAS THREE YEARS
YOUNGER THAN ME.

24:37.056 --> 24:38.808
SMARTER THAN ME,
FUNNIER THAN ME --

24:38.808 --> 24:41.100
BETTER PERSON THAN ME,
OKAY?

24:41.100 --> 24:42.982
BUT SHE DID
EVERYTHING I DID.

24:42.982 --> 24:46.365
WE WENT TO MED SCHOOL TOGETHER,
AND THAT'S WHERE WE MET RIGGS.

24:46.365 --> 24:48.367
NATE WAS MY BEST FRIEND.

24:48.367 --> 24:51.370
AND MEGAN LOVED HIM.

24:51.370 --> 24:54.574
AND HE WAS WITH HER
THE DAY THAT WE LOST HER.

24:56.325 --> 25:00.079
I TRUSTED HIM WITH HER,
AND HE WAS LIKE A BROTHER TO ME.

25:01.711 --> 25:03.543
AND HE SHOULD'VE...

25:05.795 --> 25:07.587
BUT HE DIDN'T.

25:11.761 --> 25:14.053
AND I DON'T TALK ABOUT IT.

25:14.053 --> 25:15.805
[ SLEEPING AT LAST'S "DAUGHTER"
PLAYS ]

25:15.805 --> 25:16.976
OKAY.

25:18.397 --> 25:20.309
[ SIGHS ]

25:20.309 --> 25:22.692
♪ IF ONLY YOU KNEW THE SUNLIGHT
SHINES A LITTLE BRIGHTER ♪

25:22.692 --> 25:25.855
CAN I SAY ONE THING?

25:25.855 --> 25:29.238
SHE LOVED HIM.

25:29.238 --> 25:33.412
THERE'S A REASON.
SHE LOVED HIM FOR A REASON.

25:33.412 --> 25:37.617
THAT'S WHAT I HOLD ON TO.
DEREK LOVED HER.

25:37.617 --> 25:40.209
YOUR SISTER LOVED RIGGS.

25:40.209 --> 25:41.921
SO THERE'S GOOD IN THERE.

25:41.921 --> 25:44.584
THAT MAKES HIM FAMILY.

25:44.584 --> 25:47.256
AND THAT MEANS THAT MAYBE
HE DESERVES ANOTHER CHANCE.

25:49.008 --> 25:52.431
♪ SPEAK YOUR MIND
A LITTLE LOUDER ♪

25:52.431 --> 25:55.635
♪ 'CAUSE YOU ARE ROYALTY ♪

25:55.635 --> 25:57.476
ARE YOU STILL HUNGRY?

25:57.476 --> 25:59.098
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

25:59.098 --> 26:00.680
WHAT ARE WE EATING?

26:00.680 --> 26:02.141
I COULD GO FOR A PIZZA.

26:02.141 --> 26:03.943
♪ THIS IS YOUR STORY ♪

26:03.943 --> 26:05.895
ME, TOO.

26:05.895 --> 26:11.030
♪ AND THIS IS YOUR MOMENT,
DON'T LOOK DOWN ♪

26:14.243 --> 26:15.905
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

26:15.905 --> 26:17.406
HANGING.

26:17.406 --> 26:19.158
I KICKED YOU OFF MY CASE.

26:19.158 --> 26:21.410
I KNOW.
I'M NOT GONNA OPERATE ON YOU.

26:21.410 --> 26:23.623
THEN WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

26:23.623 --> 26:25.755
I'M HOLDING YOUR HAND.

26:25.755 --> 26:28.007
FIGURED YOU'D WANT SOMEONE
TO HOLD YOUR HAND.

26:28.007 --> 26:32.051
I MEAN, IF YOU HAVE
NOTHING BETTER TO DO.

26:32.051 --> 26:34.473
♪ OUR CEILING
IS YOUR FLOOR ♪

26:34.473 --> 26:36.806
♪ AND ALL YOU GOTTA DO ♪

26:36.806 --> 26:40.139
♪ IS PUT ONE FOOT
IN FRONT OF YOU ♪

26:42.311 --> 26:44.183
♪ IF ONLY YOU KNEW ♪

26:48.938 --> 26:52.571
♪ IF ONLY YOU KNEW ♪

26:52.571 --> 26:54.994
OKAY, MAYA.
WE'RE READY TO ROLL.

26:57.496 --> 26:58.868
[ Voice breaking ]
DR. KAREV.

26:58.868 --> 27:01.120
[ BREATHING SHAKILY ]

27:02.792 --> 27:04.583
ALL RIGHT, EVERYBODY,
CLEAR THE ROOM.

27:04.583 --> 27:06.916
GIVE HER A MINUTE.

27:06.916 --> 27:08.167
OKAY.

27:08.167 --> 27:11.510
♪ OPEN YOUR EYES
A LITTLE WIDER ♪

27:11.510 --> 27:14.093
♪ SPEAK YOUR MIND
A LITTLE LOUDER ♪

27:14.093 --> 27:15.094
YOU WANT ME TO GET
YOUR MOM?

27:15.094 --> 27:18.057
[ SNIFFLES ]
NO, NO.

27:18.057 --> 27:20.970
[ CHUCKLES ]
SHE'LL JUST FREAK OUT.

27:20.970 --> 27:24.263
SHE WAS PRACTICALLY MY AGE
WHEN SHE HAD ME.

27:24.263 --> 27:26.936
AND SHE WORKS TWO JOBS
TO COVER MY BILLS

27:26.936 --> 27:29.819
AND THE GOOD INSURANCE.

27:29.819 --> 27:33.612
SHE TRIES.

27:33.612 --> 27:35.735
IF SOMETHING HAPPENS TO ME,
WILL YOU TELL HER

27:35.735 --> 27:38.117
THAT THERE'S AN ENVELOPE UNDER
MY BED WITH BANK STATEMENTS

27:38.117 --> 27:40.039
AND THE DEED TO OUR HOUSE?

27:40.039 --> 27:42.451
JUST DON'T FORGET,
OKAY?

27:42.451 --> 27:45.494
HEY, NONE OF THAT.

27:45.494 --> 27:49.048
♪ IS PUT ONE FOOT
IN FRONT OF YOU ♪

27:49.048 --> 27:51.841
OH, GOD,
I DON'T WANT TO DIE.

27:51.841 --> 27:53.753
YOU'RE NOT GONNA DIE.

27:53.753 --> 27:55.134
[ SNIFFLES ]

27:55.134 --> 27:57.556
WE BOTH KNOW
YOU CAN'T PROMISE ANYTHING.

27:57.556 --> 27:59.178
♪ AND ALL YOU GOTTA DO ♪

27:59.178 --> 28:04.804
♪ IS PUT ONE FOOT
IN FRONT OF YOU ♪

28:04.804 --> 28:07.727
♪ IF ONLY YOU KNEW ♪

28:07.727 --> 28:10.269
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

28:10.269 --> 28:11.941
YOU GOOD?

28:11.941 --> 28:13.943
♪ IF ONLY YOU KNEW ♪

28:13.943 --> 28:15.654
YEAH.

28:15.654 --> 28:17.316
LET'S DO THIS.

28:17.316 --> 28:21.240
UM, DO ME A FAVOR,
THOUGH.

28:21.240 --> 28:24.323
IF YOU'RE NOT TOO BUSY
MAKING SOME KID A BUTTHOLE,

28:24.323 --> 28:27.496
CAN YOU KEEP MY MOM COMPANY?

28:27.496 --> 28:29.919
OKAY. THANK YOU.

28:36.425 --> 28:39.889
♪ THIS IS YOUR KINGDOM,
THIS IS YOUR CROWN ♪

28:39.889 --> 28:43.302
♪ THIS IS YOUR STORY ♪

28:43.302 --> 28:50.439
♪ THIS IS YOUR MOMENT,
DON'T LOOK DOWN ♪

28:50.439 --> 28:52.191
Therapist: YOU SAID
YOU WERE GOOD AT BEING ALONE.

28:52.191 --> 28:54.273
WILL YOU STOP SAYING
WHAT I SAID?

28:54.273 --> 28:57.026
OKAY.

28:57.026 --> 28:58.567
SO, WHY ARE YOU SO ANGRY?

28:58.567 --> 29:01.280
I'M NOT.

29:01.280 --> 29:03.032
[ CHUCKLES ]

29:03.032 --> 29:03.913
OKAY.

29:05.744 --> 29:08.037
SO, HOW WAS IT?

29:08.037 --> 29:11.670
IT WAS FINE.

29:11.670 --> 29:15.925
I CHECKED ON THE KIDS,
I READ A BOOK, I WENT TO SLEEP.

29:15.925 --> 29:17.136
IT WAS GOOD ADVICE.

29:19.138 --> 29:20.589
I GOT WHAT I NEEDED.

29:20.589 --> 29:22.972
I-- IT WAS...

29:22.972 --> 29:24.934
WHAT?

29:24.934 --> 29:26.145
MM.

29:26.145 --> 29:28.307
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

29:28.307 --> 29:31.100
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS ]

29:38.948 --> 29:41.780
THEY LEFT ME ALONE.

29:53.122 --> 29:55.464
YOU SAID THE FIRST THING YOU
REMEMBER AFTER THE ATTACK WAS --

29:55.464 --> 29:56.545
PAIN.

29:58.717 --> 30:00.549
EVERYTHING HURT.

30:00.549 --> 30:03.883
NO, ACTUALLY,
YOU SAID IT WAS PEOPLE.

30:03.883 --> 30:05.975
EVERYONE WAS THERE,
YOU SAID.

30:05.975 --> 30:08.187
YEAH.
EVERY TIME I OPENED MY EYES,

30:08.187 --> 30:09.929
IT WAS LIKE THE FREAKING
"WIZARD OF OZ."

30:09.929 --> 30:11.190
EVERYONE AS THERE.

30:11.190 --> 30:12.771
MAGGIE WAS THERE.
RICHARD WAS THERE.

30:12.771 --> 30:14.143
THEY WERE THERE TO HELP.

30:14.143 --> 30:17.566
I MEAN,
THEY WERE DOING THEIR JOBS.

30:17.566 --> 30:18.817
JUST BEING GOOD DOCTORS?

30:18.817 --> 30:20.860
YEAH. DOING THEIR JOBS.

30:20.860 --> 30:22.201
LOOKING GOOD.
DRAIN IS OUT.

30:22.201 --> 30:24.493
SO AM I.
ALL RIGHT.
WOUND VAC IS OUT.

30:24.493 --> 30:26.615
LET'S REMOVE
THE LIVER PACKING.

30:26.615 --> 30:28.537
[ ALARMS BEEPING ]

30:28.537 --> 30:31.040
DAMN IT. DAMN IT.
BLOOD'S NOT CLOTTING.

30:31.040 --> 30:33.873
[ SIGHS ]
LAPS. CLAMP.

30:33.873 --> 30:35.044
CLAMP WHAT?
I CAN'T SEE A THING.

30:35.044 --> 30:36.295
THERE. RIGHT THERE.
W-WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

30:36.295 --> 30:37.957
CLAMP WHAT?
THERE'S TOO MUCH BLOOD.

30:37.957 --> 30:39.218
THAT. THAT. RIGHT THERE.
CLAMP THERE.
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT. OKAY.

30:39.218 --> 30:40.920
I GOT THE IVC,
BUT HE'S STILL BLEEDING.

30:40.920 --> 30:43.092
THERE'S TOO MUCH DAMAGE.
MORE LAPS.

30:43.092 --> 30:44.593
KEEP PACKING.
FASTER, FASTER.

30:44.593 --> 30:46.015
WHY? I'M TRYING.
I'M GONNA HAVE TO
OPEN HIM UP.

30:46.015 --> 30:46.805
SCISSORS.
W-W-WHY?

30:46.805 --> 30:48.017
BETADINE.
W-WHY?

30:48.017 --> 30:49.518
HE NEEDS
A VENOVENOUS BYPASS.

30:49.518 --> 30:50.769
HAVE YOU EVER
DONE THAT BEFORE?
IN THE FIELD.

30:50.769 --> 30:52.141
COME ON.
THERE'S NO TIME.

30:52.141 --> 30:54.063
WELL, OKAY, THEN WE'RE GONNA
NEED ANOTHER SET OF HANDS.

30:54.063 --> 30:57.066
SOMEONE PAGE PIERCE.
NO. RIGGS. GET RIGGS.

30:57.066 --> 30:58.527
ARE YOU SURE YOU WANT TO --
SOMEBODY GET RIGGS!

30:58.527 --> 31:00.439
Woman: RIGHT AWAY.

31:00.439 --> 31:02.571
SCALPEL. THANK YOU.

31:03.652 --> 31:06.155
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

31:14.293 --> 31:16.045
RIGHT TEMPLATE.

31:22.171 --> 31:23.963
OKAY. BONE SAW.

31:27.846 --> 31:29.888
[ SAW WHIRRING ]

31:37.186 --> 31:39.278
OKAY. HANG MORE FFP
AND PLATELETS.

31:39.278 --> 31:41.730
WE'LL KEEP COMPRESSIONS.
GOT IT. I GOT IT.

31:41.730 --> 31:44.323
THERE'S DAMAGE
TO THE RETROHEPATIC IVC.

31:44.323 --> 31:45.784
THE LIVER IS JUST --
Nathan:
YEAH, I GOT IT.

31:45.784 --> 31:46.946
ALL RIGHT. YOU WANT TO DO
AN END AROUND THE LIVER?

31:46.946 --> 31:48.077
THAT IS
WHAT I WAS THINKING.

31:48.077 --> 31:49.368
OKAY, SET UP THE BIOPUMP.

31:49.368 --> 31:50.829
WE'RE GONNA NEED
VENOUS CANNULAS.
ON IT.

31:50.829 --> 31:51.790
YOU GOT THE PORTAL?
YEP.

31:51.790 --> 31:53.582
I GOT THE SVC.

31:53.582 --> 31:55.034
HERE.
CHEERS.

31:55.034 --> 31:56.915
HUNT CALLED FOR HIM?
YEAH,
THIS COULD GET UGLY.

31:56.915 --> 31:58.877
IF YOU WANT, I CAN...

31:58.877 --> 32:01.000
CLAMPS.
FORCEPS.

32:03.963 --> 32:05.344
OKAY.
I'M GONNA NEED --

32:05.344 --> 32:07.096
METZ.

32:11.850 --> 32:13.012
POTTS.

32:13.012 --> 32:14.143
MM-HMM.

32:16.395 --> 32:19.398
WE'RE GONNA NEED TO DO A --
PURSE STRING AFTER BYPASS.

32:19.398 --> 32:21.060
MM-HMM.

32:21.060 --> 32:23.112
I CAN HELP YOU GUYS
IF YOU NEED IT.

32:23.112 --> 32:25.404
OKAY, HERE, YOU CAN
HOLD THE CANNULAS.
OKAY.

32:25.404 --> 32:28.327
AND...
SET HERE.

32:28.327 --> 32:31.410
GO.

32:31.410 --> 32:33.662
LINES UP.

32:33.662 --> 32:34.623
CLAMPING.
MM-HMM.

32:39.538 --> 32:40.959
OOH.
THERE YOU GO.

32:40.959 --> 32:42.541
ALL RIGHT. GOOD.

32:42.541 --> 32:44.133
OKAY.

32:45.884 --> 32:47.586
GOOD.
SET.

32:47.586 --> 32:48.847
AND...

32:48.847 --> 32:50.139
Both:
THREE, TWO, ONE.

32:56.685 --> 32:57.936
Both: FLOW.

33:00.359 --> 33:01.360
NOT BAD.

33:03.272 --> 33:05.064
Both: 3/0 PROLENE.

33:13.202 --> 33:17.496
MEREDITH, HOW DID IT FEEL
FOR YOU?

33:17.496 --> 33:20.079
YOU KNOW, STUCK THERE,
CAN'T MOVE, CAN'T HEAR,

33:20.079 --> 33:23.622
CAN'T SPEAK,
JUST WATCHING EVERYONE?

33:23.622 --> 33:26.295
CRAPPY.

33:26.295 --> 33:28.337
YOU USE THAT WORD A LOT.

33:28.337 --> 33:30.179
CAN YOU TRY
A DIFFERENT ONE?

33:30.179 --> 33:33.632
I DON'T KNOW.
OPEN. EXPOSED. ALONE.

33:33.632 --> 33:34.803
YEAH,
BUT YOU WEREN'T ALONE.

33:34.803 --> 33:37.766
THEY WERE ALL THERE.

33:53.652 --> 33:56.075
THEY ALL HAD YOU.

33:56.075 --> 33:57.496
SO, I ASK ONCE AGAIN...

33:59.158 --> 34:00.659
...HOW DID IT FEEL
FOR YOU?

34:00.659 --> 34:01.960
YEAH.

34:01.960 --> 34:04.083
CRAPPY REALLY IS
THE BEST WORD.

34:08.837 --> 34:10.429
Jo: WOW.

34:10.429 --> 34:12.721
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:12.721 --> 34:14.343
THANK YOU.

34:14.343 --> 34:16.555
OKAY.

34:16.555 --> 34:17.976
[ SIGHS ]

34:23.272 --> 34:25.314
OH, SHOOT.

34:25.314 --> 34:27.186
UGH.
SHOOT. DAMN IT!

34:27.186 --> 34:28.527
WHAT?
WHAT'S GOING ON?

34:28.527 --> 34:29.858
IT'S NOT FITTING.

34:29.858 --> 34:31.400
HOW IS THAT POSSIBLE?
IT'S CUSTOM-MADE FOR HER.

34:31.400 --> 34:32.741
NO, IT'S --
THE RIBS ARE FINE.

34:32.741 --> 34:34.403
IT'S LIKE A FITTED SHEET
ON A BED.

34:34.403 --> 34:36.495
ONCE YOU ATTACH ONE SIDE --
THE OTHER SIDE POPS OUT.

34:36.495 --> 34:38.957
YEAH, AND ANOTHER SET'S
GONNA TAKE 14 HOURS TO PRINT.

34:38.957 --> 34:40.659
CAN WE LEAVE HER OPEN
FOR THAT LONG?
N-NO. NO.

34:40.659 --> 34:43.412
IT WILL LEAVE HER AT RISK
FOR POST-OPT INFECTION, CLOTS.

34:43.412 --> 34:45.124
[ SIGHS ]
SO, NOW WHAT?

34:45.124 --> 34:46.585
UH...

34:51.300 --> 34:53.342
THEY WANT TO RETRACT
HER RIB CAGE,

34:53.342 --> 34:55.674
PULL IT OPEN TO MAKE ENOUGH
SPACE FOR THE NEW RIBS TO FIT.

34:55.674 --> 34:57.306
NO.

34:57.306 --> 35:00.219
I MEAN, THEY COULD SLIP AND
PUNCTURE HER LUNG AND HER HEART.

35:00.219 --> 35:02.060
WE KNOW.
OR CRACK HER RIBS.

35:02.060 --> 35:03.142
AND IF SHE'S UNDER
TOO LONG,

35:03.142 --> 35:04.353
THEY'LL NEVER GET HER
OFF THE VENT.

35:04.353 --> 35:06.315
ALEX, EITHER THIS
OR WE GO BACK TO THE PLATES.

35:06.315 --> 35:08.647
WHICH IS EXACTLY
WHAT SHE DOESN'T WANT.

35:08.647 --> 35:10.859
THAT'S WHY THEY WANTED TO CHECK
BEFORE THEY WENT AHEAD.

35:13.322 --> 35:14.613
I DON'T WANT TO WAKE HER UP
AND ASK HER.

35:14.613 --> 35:16.445
SHE SIGNED A CONSENT.

35:16.445 --> 35:17.906
WE DON'T NEED
HER PERMISSION.

35:17.906 --> 35:21.290
THEY WANTED
TO CHECK WITH YOU.

35:21.290 --> 35:23.242
MY MOM WAS JUST LIKE HER.

35:23.242 --> 35:25.204
I HAD TO TAKE CARE
OF EVERYTHING.

35:25.204 --> 35:27.956
MAKES A GIRL GLAD SHE WAS LEFT
IN A STROLLER AT A FIRE STATION.

35:29.508 --> 35:32.551
[ LAUGHS ]

35:32.551 --> 35:33.422
MADE YOU TOUGH.

35:33.422 --> 35:35.093
MM.

35:39.097 --> 35:40.759
MAYA'S TOUGH.

35:40.759 --> 35:42.761
SHE CAN DO IT.

35:44.062 --> 35:46.725
OKAY. ON MY COUNT.
ONE, TWO, THREE.

35:46.725 --> 35:49.318
[ GRUNTING ]

35:49.318 --> 35:50.649
CAREFUL NOT TO COMPRESS
HER HEART.

35:50.649 --> 35:51.860
I'M TRYING.

35:51.860 --> 35:53.322
WILSON, I KNOW THAT YOU CAN
PULL HARDER THAN THAT.

35:53.322 --> 35:56.034
OKAY.
AGAIN. ONE, TWO, THREE.

35:56.034 --> 35:58.777
[ GRUNTING ]
OKAY. COME ON.

35:58.777 --> 36:00.078
[ MONITORS BEEPING ]

36:00.078 --> 36:02.451
OH, CRAP.
SHE'S BEEN UNDER TOO LONG.

36:02.451 --> 36:03.492
SHE'S FLUID OVERLOADED.

36:03.492 --> 36:04.623
HER HEART'S
BEGINNING TO FAIL.

36:04.623 --> 36:05.914
[ GRUNTS ]

36:05.914 --> 36:07.876
AND DONE HERE.

36:07.876 --> 36:10.669
GOOD? KEPNER,
WOULD YOU FINISH UP CLOSING?

36:10.669 --> 36:12.090
UH, YEAH.
YEAH, OF COURSE.

36:12.090 --> 36:15.053
UH...THAT WAS...

36:15.053 --> 36:17.256
INSANE. HAVE YOU EVER SEEN
ANYTHING LIKE THAT?

36:17.256 --> 36:20.219
IT'S LIKE THEY FORMED
ONE SUPER SURGEON.

36:23.682 --> 36:26.104
THAT WAS A THING OF BEAUTY.

36:26.104 --> 36:28.357
IT WAS LIKE
WATCHING BALLET.

36:28.357 --> 36:31.310
UH, KEPNER,
I THINK YOU OWE ME AN APOLOGY.

36:34.483 --> 36:36.615
[ Muffled ] JUST BECAUSE
WE SAVED A PATIENT

36:36.615 --> 36:37.986
DOESN'T MEAN
THINGS ARE BACK...

36:37.986 --> 36:41.320
DO I, THOUGH?

36:41.320 --> 36:43.081
YOU DIDN'T SCREW THIS UP
BECAUSE I WAS THERE.

36:43.081 --> 36:45.123
IF I WASN'T THERE,
THAT'S WHEN --

36:45.123 --> 36:45.994
Nathan:
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA. STOP.

36:45.994 --> 36:47.286
YEAH, OKAY.

36:47.286 --> 36:49.958
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

36:51.790 --> 36:55.384
ALL I KNOW IS WHEN THEY'RE ALL
AT MY HOUSE, I WANT THEM GONE.

36:55.384 --> 36:58.597
AND THEN, WHEN THEY LEAVE,
I DON'T FEEL ANY BETTER.

36:58.597 --> 37:00.138
SO, WHAT,
DOES THAT MAKE ME CRAZY?

37:00.138 --> 37:01.890
I WAS GONNA SAY
IT MAKES YOU HUMAN.

37:01.890 --> 37:03.101
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

37:03.101 --> 37:05.103
I AM VERY GOOD
AT BEING ALONE.

37:05.103 --> 37:07.436
I'VE TAUGHT MYSELF
HOW TO DO IT.

37:07.436 --> 37:10.108
AND I DON'T MEAN MY KIDS.
I LOVE MY KIDS.

37:10.108 --> 37:13.692
AND I HAVE MY CLASS
AND MY WORK.

37:13.692 --> 37:15.274
I HAVE MOVED ON.

37:15.274 --> 37:19.528
YOU SEE, BUT, UH,
A WIDOW REALLY HASN'T MOVED ON.

37:19.528 --> 37:21.119
SHE'S STILL
SORT OF MARRIED.

37:21.119 --> 37:22.911
SHE'S JUST MARRIED
TO A DEAD GUY.

37:22.911 --> 37:25.123
YOU'RE NOT MARRIED
ANYMORE.

37:25.123 --> 37:27.956
AND YOU'RE NOT A WIDOW
ANYMORE.

37:27.956 --> 37:29.998
SO, WHAT ARE YOU?

37:44.433 --> 37:46.765
I DON'T KNOW.

37:59.398 --> 38:01.660
OKAY, SO,
WHAT HAPPENS NOW?

38:01.660 --> 38:03.492
I DON'T KNOW.

38:03.492 --> 38:05.574
THAT'S UP TO YOU.

38:05.574 --> 38:08.327
[ CRYING ]

38:09.998 --> 38:11.540
SHE DID GREAT.

38:11.540 --> 38:14.172
THEY WERE ABLE TO DO
EXACTLY WHAT SHE WANTED.

38:14.172 --> 38:17.175
YOU CAN GO IN.

38:17.175 --> 38:19.418
SHE JUST LOOKS SO...

38:19.418 --> 38:21.970
[ CRYING ]

38:21.970 --> 38:23.472
WELL, WHY DON'T YOU GO
GET SOME COFFEE

38:23.472 --> 38:26.134
AND MEET US BACK HERE
WHEN YOU'VE HAD SOME TIME, OKAY?

38:26.134 --> 38:27.926
[ SNIFFLES ]

38:29.428 --> 38:30.228
COME ON.

38:33.392 --> 38:34.773
SURGICAL INCISION
LOOKS GOOD.

38:34.773 --> 38:36.935
I PUT HER ON A LASIX DRIP,

38:36.935 --> 38:38.777
AND I'LL BE BACK IN AN HOUR
TO CHECK HER I's AND O's.

38:38.777 --> 38:40.238
THANKS.

38:40.238 --> 38:42.361
OKAY.

38:46.945 --> 38:48.156
YOUR MOM
WILL BE BACK SOON.

38:48.156 --> 38:51.580
CHECK THIS OUT,
IRON MAN.

38:52.751 --> 38:55.374
YOU WERE A BADASS TODAY.

38:59.958 --> 39:02.340
WE CAN KEEP GOING.

39:02.340 --> 39:04.262
OR...

39:04.262 --> 39:05.424
I FEEL GOOD.

39:05.424 --> 39:07.265
YOU FEEL GOOD?

39:07.265 --> 39:08.266
I DON'T.

39:08.266 --> 39:10.138
I MEAN,
I FEEL COMFORTABLE

39:10.138 --> 39:12.771
SIGNING THE PAPERS
FOR DR. BAILEY.

39:12.771 --> 39:15.524
YOU SHOW NO SIGNS OF PTSD.

39:15.524 --> 39:17.686
AND YOU'RE
CERTAINLY CAPABLE

39:17.686 --> 39:19.738
OF TAKING CARE
OF YOUR PATIENTS...

39:19.738 --> 39:21.400
AND YOURSELF.

39:21.400 --> 39:23.442
BUT I FEEL TERRIBLE.

39:23.442 --> 39:26.074
I CAME IN HERE,
AND I FELT GREAT.

39:26.074 --> 39:29.578
AND NOW I DON'T KNOW WHO I AM
OR WHAT I WANT.

39:29.578 --> 39:31.660
WELL, YOU WANTED
A TAPE-AND-GLUE GUY.

39:31.660 --> 39:35.083
AND I THINK YOU'RE
HOLDING UP PRETTY WELL.

39:37.456 --> 39:40.168
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

39:40.168 --> 39:40.959
RICHARD.

39:40.959 --> 39:43.842
PIERCE. DeLUCA.

39:43.842 --> 39:44.763
GOOD NIGHT.
SIR.

39:44.763 --> 39:46.595
'NIGHT.

39:50.719 --> 39:52.771
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

39:54.352 --> 39:56.605
[ SIGHS ]

39:56.605 --> 40:00.018
♪ NA-NA, NA-NA, NA-NA,
NA-NA, NA, NA ♪

40:00.018 --> 40:03.191
♪ NA-NA, NA-NA, NA-NA,
NA-NA, NA, NA ♪

40:03.191 --> 40:04.573
♪ NA-NA, NA-NA, NA-NA,
NA-NA, NA, NA ♪

40:04.573 --> 40:05.984
YOU'RE REALLY BAD AT THIS.

40:05.984 --> 40:07.616
YOU SHOULD HAVE GOTTEN
A WOMAN.

40:07.616 --> 40:10.158
WHAT DO I DO NOW?

40:10.158 --> 40:11.159
I DON'T KNOW.

40:11.159 --> 40:14.122
♪ MAMA'LL BE BACK
IN A MINUTE ♪

40:14.122 --> 40:17.415
♪ GOT TO HUSTLE AND HANDLE
OUR BUSINESS ♪

40:17.415 --> 40:20.338
♪ I'LL BE RIGHT BACK
WHEN I'M DONE ♪

40:20.338 --> 40:23.632
♪ I GOTTA RUN, RUN,
RUN, RUN, BABY ♪

40:23.632 --> 40:26.595
I MISS YOU.

40:26.595 --> 40:31.760
♪ MAMA'S GOOD
AND YOU KNOW MAMA'S ABLE ♪

40:31.760 --> 40:33.101
♪ NA-NA, NA-NA, NA-NA,
NA-NA, NA, NA ♪

40:33.101 --> 40:35.183
♪ I'VE GOTTA RUN,
RUN, RUN, RUN ♪

40:35.183 --> 40:38.226
♪ I'M SUPERWOMAN,
FLYIN' THROUGH THE CITY ♪

40:38.226 --> 40:40.058
♪ THERE'S ONLY ONE WAY
TO MAKE... ♪

40:40.058 --> 40:42.941
MEREDITH, YOU GOT REALLY GOOD
AT BEING ALONE.

40:45.564 --> 40:48.617
BUT SOMETHING TERRIBLE
HAPPENED TO YOU,

40:48.617 --> 40:51.369
AND THEY WERE ALL THERE.

40:53.532 --> 40:55.664
AND THEY STILL ARE.

40:55.664 --> 40:58.036
♪ 'CAUSE IT LOOKS LIKE
YOU COULD BE THE ONE ♪

40:58.036 --> 41:00.959
ARE YOU SAYING...

41:00.959 --> 41:02.961
I CAN'T BE ALONE ANYMORE?

41:02.961 --> 41:06.134
NO, I THINK YOU CAN.

41:06.134 --> 41:07.886
I JUST DON'T THINK
YOU WANT TO BE.

41:07.886 --> 41:11.299
♪ I'LL BE RIGHT
BACK WHEN I'M DONE ♪

41:11.299 --> 41:13.552
♪ I GOTTA RUN,
RUN, RUN, RUN ♪

41:13.552 --> 41:14.723
CAN WE GO?

41:14.723 --> 41:16.054
NO, HE'S --
HE'S COMING.

41:16.054 --> 41:17.435
HE'S COMING.

41:17.435 --> 41:18.226
WHAT DO YOU HAVE TO DO?

41:19.518 --> 41:21.229
OH, YOU HAVE SOMEONE TO DO.

41:21.229 --> 41:23.562
[ CHUCKLES ]
WE ARE NOT TALKING
ABOUT THAT.

41:23.562 --> 41:25.524
[ CHUCKLES ]

41:25.524 --> 41:26.945
ARE YOU OKAY?

41:26.945 --> 41:29.447
FINALLY.

41:29.447 --> 41:31.319
WHAT?

41:31.319 --> 41:33.662
OH, COME ON.

41:33.662 --> 41:36.164
IT'S BEEN A LONG DAY.
CAN WE JUST --

41:39.788 --> 41:44.793
Therapist:
YOU TOLD ME THAT ANY DAY SOMEONE
DOESN'T DIE IS A GOOD DAY.

41:44.793 --> 41:47.546
YOU ARE ALIVE.

41:47.546 --> 41:50.388
SO...HAVE A GOOD DAY.

41:50.388 --> 41:52.841
Maggie: WHAT ARE WE DOING?
DO YOU WANT TO HANG OUT?

41:52.841 --> 41:56.184
BUT WHAT THE HELL
DO I DO NOW?

41:56.184 --> 42:01.309
WELL...
THE TRUTH IS A LITTLE SCARY.

42:01.309 --> 42:06.985
THE TRUTH IS...
YOU CAN DO ANYTHING YOU WANT.

42:06.985 --> 42:09.608
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO DO?

42:09.608 --> 42:11.489
♪ I GOTTA RUN,
RUN, RUN, RUN, RUN ♪

42:11.489 --> 42:20.368
♪ RUN, RUN, RUN, RUN,
RUN, RUN, RUN, BABY ♪
